CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 28, 1960, pg. 2, reads: "Duff St. Club Succeeds - Believing that the city was neglecting their community, residents of Duff St. organized a block club and began vigorously protesting. One of the objects was this abandoned house at 630 Duff St.  The club succeeded two weeks after its organization when the city began tearing down the house... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Man on roof of house being demolished, 630 Duff Street, next to house with striped awnings, Hill District
